article.headline: Stephen F. Austin 84, Howard Payne 46
article.story: NACOGDOCHES, Texas (AP) -- Marcus Clark scored 25 points and Josh Porter added 21 to lead Stephen F. Austin to an 84-46 victory over Howard Payne on Thursday night. Clark hit 11-of-15 shots from the field and all three of his free throws to match his career high. Porter scored 15 of his points on 3-pointers. The Lumberjacks (5-5) led from the start and took a 49-20 lead at halftime. John Berkman and Lee Scott each scored seven points to lead Howard Payne (2-7). Stephen F. Austin shot 49 percent from the field for the game to 30 percent for Howard Payne.
